Apparently, the population of a little known town in Slovenia was quite excited too.Sevnica, in the centre of the country, is the home town of the next US First Lady, Melania Trump, born there in 1970. For all his garishness & vulgarity, Trump is a master hotelierWhile Trump has been a figure of contention for months, just before the election, the town's mayor was quoted by Reuters as saying, "The global attention is positive because Sevnica is developing into a tourist destination."Sevnica sits on the bank of the Sava River in the charming Sava Valley.Its top attraction is its castle, dating back possibly to the 1,100s - and soon, perhaps, the apartment block where Melania lived with her family as a child.Asked for his feelings on the result this week, the mayor declared, "We are very satisfied."